Currently the feature of migration for user directory is pretty simple perhaps there could be certain improvement to be implemented in the future for better process of the migration:

h5. Feedback from customer:
{panel}
- I find that the documentation of the migration is thin. It should have expressly stated that the internal directory will not serve as a *Fallback*. 
- The migration script should have first performed a *check* on what users are missing in the AD directory and should give a report of what users are missing to the Admin performing the migration. It should provide the opportunity to cancel the migration. In our case, we have about 330 users and the migration failed for about 40, that we know of.
- Similar to the previous point, JIRA should provide a report independent of a migration process on the JIRA users missing in the external directory. Only with the knowledge of which accounts are missing can we begin the process of applying for new AD accounts.  Related to that is an issue that I have experienced probably 20 times since the migration: We get a report from a user and the user says he or she cannot log in. As a JIRA admin and not an AD admin I have no way of knowing if the problem is because the user has forgotten his JIRA internal directory password or because the AD entry is missing altogether.
{panel}

